    <td valign="top"><blockquote><a href="profile.php?id=0000000018">Gaunja</a> said:<br><hr>The website looks fawking awesome bro. Thanks a bunch, much appreciated. Only thing that could be worked on is a way for everyone to update their level from the members list with their login or something. Dunno<hr></blockquote>The way I have the member list setup now is by periodically dumping the guild manager window in EQ to a text file, and placing the text file to the website. The program that runs the website then reads the file every time you go to the list. As long as its updated often enough, the levels should always be correct. I also added a security feature, which may confuse some people: I figured since we are on a PvP server we shouldn't make it easy for anyone to get ahold of the levels of everyone in our guild, so if you are not logged into the site (as in not a member, just a visitor) all the levels will show up as 0, and if you are logged in you will see the real levels. Neat, huh?<br><br>Any suggestions are welcome though... I am thinking about adding the ability to link characters to member accounts, and allow more than one character to be linked to an account. Also I have other ideas that I may post for comment on this board. Tell me what you think.<br><br>____________________<br><a href="mailto:examancer@cox.net">Examancer</a> - the admin.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=658323" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.examancer.com/images/exapic.jpg" border=0></a>
