    <td valign="top">it ended up not taking me very much time, so the events board is now password protected. I ended up only allowing <i>verified</i> guild members to get to the board. I have not yet come up with a good way to verify that users are guild members, so I have been doing it by hand as they register.<br><br>Since you are also an admin, you can verify users also. You must go to their profile (which can be accessed by clicking on there name on a forum post of theirs), and since you are admin you will see a button that says "change user type". Click that and change to "2 (guild member)" or "3 (officer)" depending on their status.<br><br>____________________<br><a href="mailto:examancer@cox.net">Examancer</a> - the admin.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=658323" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.examancer.com/images/exapic.jpg" border=0></a>
